The bound |ad + bc + ca − db| ≤ 2 holds. Equality |ad + bc + ca − db| = 2 occurs exactly in the following cases:
- a = b = ±1 and c = ±1 (with d arbitrary in [−1, 1]);
- a = −b = ±1 and d = ±1 (with c arbitrary in [−1, 1]);
- a = ±1, |b| < 1, and c = d = ±1;
- b = ±1, |a| < 1, and c = −d = ±1.
